{
  "text": "The dg category C dg (A) is a pretriangulated dg category in the sense of [CITATION_1] Section 4.3] . Let K(A) := H 0 C dg (A) be the homotopy category of C dg (A), see [CITATION_2] Section 2.2] . Precisely, the objects of K(A) are dg A-modules, and for two dg A-modules M and N we have",
